ðŸ”§ Steps to Disable Windows Hello for Business (PIN) via Intune

1. Go to Microsoft Intune Admin Center
URL: https://intune.microsoft.com
2. Create a Configuration Profile
Platform: Windows 10 and later
Profile type: Settings catalog
3. Configure the Settings
In the Settings picker, search for Windows Hello for Business.
Add the following settings:
Setting	Value
Use Windows Hello for Business	Disabled
Configure Windows Hello for Business	Disabled
This will disable the use of PIN, facial recognition, and fingerprint sign-in.

4. Assign the Profile
Assign it to the device group or user group you want to target.
